Joseph Olaoluwa The Lagos State Government has announced the closure of another level crossing to facilitate the construction of the ongoing Lagos-Ibadan standard gauge rail line. It said in a statement on Friday that “the Abule level crossing towards the Apapa end of the railway project will be closed from Saturday, November 21st, to Sunday, November 22nd, 2020.” It explained that in line with the Nigerian Railway Modernisation Project (Lagos-Ibadan section) with extension to Lagos Port at Apapa, “that the construction company, China Civil Engineering Construction Company Nigeria Limited, would commence the track construction at 5:00am and finish by 8pm the next day.” Also, the new Costain Bridge is expected to be opened to all motorists on the 19th of November to serve as an alternative route for motorists plying the axis to aid their movement. Copyright PUNCH.
